pecially since existing tests involve `DnsSettingsTest`. I wonder if the compile failure is about reflective access in Java 25.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Scala dependencies**\\n\\nI'm considering the tests in Scala and whether I need the scala-compiler dependency and possibly a plugin for Scala artifacts. It sounds like the project already adds scala-library and compiler, although I'm not entirely sure about the generated test scaffold. The artifact has a Scala API and existing tests, but I noticed the Java API for actors exists too, with documentation available. So, I think meaningful coverage can come from Java tests without requiring extra dependencies beyond the runtime. I might need to inspect classes to double-check the Java API.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jvgvDlfVcgHFrSl0NxD1mYiZ|fc_09493134288681e1016a4077df04008190932d0ecd64abfb85", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, re\nurls=[\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/actors.html',\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/actors.html#dependency',\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/typed/actors.html',\n]\nfor u in urls:\n print('\\n---',u)\n try:\n  s=urllib.request.urlopen(u,timeout=20).read().decode('utf-8','replace')\n  text=re.sub('<[^>]+>',' ',s)\n  text=re.sub(r'\\s+',' ',text)\n  for term in ['pekko-actor_2.13','ActorSystem', 'dependency', 'Docker', 'reference.conf']:\n   i=text.find(term)\n   print(term, i, text[max(0,i-300):i+600] if i!=-1 else '')\n except Exception as e: print('ERR',e)\nPY", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1321, "output": 1145, "cacheRead": 19456, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21922, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782609872689, "responseId": "resp_09493134288681e1016a4077d157308190aa72ec56d94f3ea9"}}
